      "content": [
        {
          "type": "title",
          "value": "Origins: bin1 dou6 jan4"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "To ask someone what country they are from, you ask if they are a 'where person' (<strong>邊度人</strong> - bin1 dou6 jan4)."
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "邊度人？",
          "romanization": "bin1 dou6 jan4?",
          "translation": "From where? (Nationality)"
        },
        {
          "type": "title",
          "value": "Nationalities"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Simply add <strong>人</strong> (jan4 - person) to the end of a country name to state a nationality."
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "美國",
          "romanization": "mei5 gwok3",
          "translation": "USA"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "英國",
          "romanization": "jing1 gwok3",
          "translation": "UK"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "美國人",
          "romanization": "mei5 gwok3 jan4",
          "translation": "American person"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "英國人",
          "romanization": "jing1 gwok3 jan4",
          "translation": "British person"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "reading",
      "exerciseId": "6.3.2"
    },
    {
